  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stop the Spread COVID-19 in Amhara, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of Amref&apos;s co-ordinated response to Stop the Spread and Flatten the Curve in 8 priority countries across Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to train 8,000 health extension workers (HEWs) in the Amhara region through Amref&apos;s mobile digital training platform LEAP. The HEWs will be trained using a COVID-19 curriculum developed with the MoH focussing on key topics including community-based tracing, prevention and management of COVID-19, and measures to contain the spread.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be directly targeting 8,000 HEWs to gain knowledge that will indirectly benefit households in the Amhara region</narrative>
  </description>
